╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

SPECIFICATION:
  Background: μ(d,y) = exp(β₀ + γ·log(pop) + δ·poverty + Σ β_year)
  Triggering: α(marks) = exp(β₀_trig + β_riot + β_fatal + β_student + β_labor)
  Kernel: g(Δt) = p·exp(-β_fast·Δt) + (1-p)·exp(-β_slow·Δt)  [MIXED!]
  Intensity: λ(t) = μ(d,y) + Σ α(marks_i) · g(t - t_i)

HYPOTHESIS:
  → Two distinct timescales: fast (days) + slow (weeks/months)
  → Most contagion is short-term (p ≈ 0.7-0.9)
  → Resolves single exponential's misspecification

